    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely chop (or grate) the<strong> remaining garlic</strong> and chop your <strong>parsley</strong> finely, including the stalks</p><p>Combine your <strong>panko breadcrumbs </strong>in a bowl with <strong>half</strong> the <strong>chopped parsley</strong>, <strong>half</strong> your <strong>smoked paprika </strong>(you'll use the rest later!), 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp] </span><strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper </strong>– this is your <strong>herby breadcrumb mixture</strong></p><p>Combine the <strong>chopped garlic </strong>and <strong>mayo </strong>in a bowl with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tsp]</span> <strong>cold water </strong>– this is your <strong>aioli</strong></p>",
